Heat grill. Season steaks with salt and pepper. Place steaks on grill over medium-high heat. Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes, turning once, for medium rare or to desired doneness. Meanwhile, melt Parmesan butter in medium skillet over medium heat. Add shrimp and cook 4 to 6 minutes, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are pink and firm. Place grilled steaks on serving plates; top with shrimp.